==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Holyday
<hw>Ho"ly*day`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
religious festival.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A secular festival; a holiday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Holiday</xex> is the preferable and prevailing
spelling in the second sense. The spelling <xex>holy day or
holyday</xex> in often used in the first sense.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holystone</ent>⟦br⟧
